  "text": "The Kafka ProduceRequest write chain flows through the following sequence:\n\n1. **Client-Side Producer (KafkaProducer)**: The user calls KafkaProducer.send() in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/KafkaProducer.java (line 941), which is the public API for sending records. This method intercepts the record and delegates to KafkaProducer.doSend() (line 974).\n\n2. **Record Accumulation (RecordAccumulator)**: Within doSend(), at line 1029, KafkaProducer calls RecordAccumulator.append() in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java (line 275). This method batches individual records into MemoryRecords for efficient network transmission, handling partition selection, buffer allocation, and batch creation.\n\n3. **Producer Sender Thread (Sender)**: The Sender.run() thread in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java periodically calls sendProducerData() (line 357) to send accumulated batches. This method gets ready batches using accumulator.ready() and accumulator.drain(), then calls sendProduceRequest() to create ProduceRequest objects and send them via the network.\n\n4. **Network Layer (NetworkClient)**: At line 914 in Sender.sendProduceRequest(), the NetworkClient.send() method is invoked in clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/NetworkClient.java (line 541). This method wraps the request, determines the appropriate protocol version, and calls the private doSend() (line 601) which adds the request to inFlightRequests and sends it via selector.send() at line 617.\n\n5. **Broker-Side Replica Manager (ReplicaManager)**: On the broker side, when the ProduceRequest arrives, ReplicaManager.appendRecords() in core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala (line 674) is invoked. This method calls appendRecordsToLeader() (line 627), which in turn calls appendToLocalLog() (line 1370). The appendToLocalLog() method iterates through the partitions and calls partition.appendRecordsToLeader() (line 1408) to perform the actual log append operation, appending the records to the partition's log storage.\n\nThis write chain ensures efficient batching on the producer side, reliable network transport, and persistent storage on the broker side."
}

